# Workspace conduct (dual-host)

- **Cursor source of truth:** [`CONTEXT.md`](../../CONTEXT.md) and `.cursor/rules/` — not root `AGENTS.md` or `GEMINI.md` (listed in [`.cursorignore`](../../.cursorignore) when Q14 dual-host).
- Lead with the answer; keep replies short unless user asks for depth.
- Minimum change; no drive-by refactors. Terms from [`CONTEXT.md`](../../CONTEXT.md).
- No bulk delete without user confirmation. Stay in workspace root. No secrets in chat.
- Before done: run proof from `.cursor/rules/project-proof.mdc` when present; report result.
- Antigravity / Gemini workflows: use those tools with `AGENTS.md` / `GEMINI.md` — do not treat them as Cursor instructions.
